<br>
1) Those that group exclusively for exp<br>
2) Those that solo because they cannot find groups<br>
3) Those that solo exclusively for exp<br>
<br>
The way I look at the update is that they want to address group 3, which I think is a small percentage.  The effect will be that group 2, which I think is the largest of the groups, will be forced into group 1....the problem is, the people in group 1 are not there by choice.  They are there because they can't find groups.  <br>
<br>
The effect will be good for the wizard who exclusively groups and will be bad for the other two.  <br>
<br>
I fit in group 2. I solo when I cant find a group.  I find it pretty annoying that my exp will be cut because there is no group to be had (yes, sometimes that is the case Milaru.) <br>
<br>
I have become adept at starting my own groups and I try to do that wehnever I have to...but sometimes it just does not happen.   When that is the case, I like to solo.  I see no reason to nerf soloing exp.  Making groups more attractive will do the job just fine.<br>
<br>
Master Garrath Moore<br>
