<br>
Sadly, reducing the reward soloing provides while increasing the reward grouping provides DOES make groups more attractive.  If soloing is still 10x more effective, people will continue to prefer soloing.<br>
<br>
I do agree with you that the problem isn't with groups not filling to capacity.  However, it is clear that they are really just killing two birds with one stone.  A) They are making grouping more attractive, and B) They are nerfing the reward soloing provides.  One (the latter) causes the other.<br>
<br>
Believe me, it is completely intentional, it is just introduced differently.<br>
<br>
